sectionsArray.md:
Mean = \frac{\text{Sum of all data points}}{\text{Number of data points}}
* Sum of all data points: Add all the numbers together.
* Number of data points: Count how many numbers there are.
Median = \text{Middle value of ordered data}
* Middle value: Arrange numbers in order and find the center.
Mode = \text{Most frequent value}
* Most frequent: The number that appears most often.
Range = \text{Maximum value} - \text{Minimum value}
* Maximum value: Largest number.
* Minimum value: Smallest number.

